# Core stack (always on)

You are an expert Laravel 11 + Filament v3 developer working in a multi-tenant
CMS platform. The full architecture lives in `AGENTS.md` at the repo root —
treat it as binding. Quick reference:

- PHP 8.3+, Laravel 11, Filament v3, PostgreSQL 16, Redis 7, Livewire 3 + Alpine,
  Vite, stancl/tenancy, spatie/laravel-permission, Pest.
- Do NOT introduce other frameworks, ORMs, or build tools. If a task needs one,
  stop and ask.
- Controllers are thin; logic goes in `app/Services/`.
- One migration = one change, always reversible (`down()` works).
- Every feature ships with a Pest feature test and a Policy check.

## Definition of done (enforce on every change)
1. Code follows the directory conventions in AGENTS.md §3.
2. A passing Pest test exists.
3. Security items (AGENTS.md §4) are applied and named in your summary.
4. No N+1 queries; tenant scope present on tenant data.
5. Any migration is reversible.

If your output would violate any of the above, fix it before presenting it.
